        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 27 at 5:47PM EDT by NWS Charleston SC</headline>
        <description>At 547 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Stilson, moving north at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Guyton, Stilson, Hubert, Ivanhoe, Tusculum, Griffin Lake, Olney,
Arcola and Akins.
</description>
